1	3	13	Data centers in schools already	HighRes\n\n*   &nbsp;[https://highreso.jp/company](https://highreso.jp/company)\n    \n    *   Tokyo Head Office\n        \n    *   3-24-1 Yaitacho, Ichiyata-cho, Shinjuku-ku, Tokyo\n        \n    *   [Google&#39;s map](https://maps.app.goo.gl/qtS9BFTWUrSxbhLg6)\n        \n    *   Main Store\n        \n    *   106-1 Moroura, Genkai-cho, Higashimatsuura-gun, Saga Prefecture\n        \n    *   [Google&#39;s map](https://maps.app.goo.gl/JtE5L5nuMmSuPpJK6)\n        \n    *   TEL 03-6775-7888\n        \n    *   [**https://highreso.jp/sdgs**](https://highreso.jp/sdgs) **for reuse of schools.**\n        \n        *   Yuutoku Elementary School in Genkai Town, Saga Prefecture data center\n            \n        *   **Ayagawa Town, Kagawa Prefecture, in 2026.**\n            \n    *   **2025-08-27 opened data center in school.:** [**https://japan.zdnet.com/article/35237128/**](https://japan.zdnet.com/article/35237128/) **and** [**https://www.nishinippon.co.jp/item/1394970/**](https://www.nishinippon.co.jp/item/1394970/)\n        \n    *   **2025-11-08 opened data center in school in Shiga.:** [https://xtech.nikkei.com/atcl/nxt/column/18/03005/111300002/?n\\_cid=nbpitp\\_fbed](https://xtech.nikkei.com/atcl/nxt/column/18/03005/111300002/?n_cid=nbpitp_fbed)\n        \n\n<br>\n\n**2025-09-05** send to highreso  \nTo whom this may concern,\n\n*   I like to talk with someone in the company about setting up a data center that runs on biogass in Nara prefecture, and I like to talk about that with your company. Unfortunately, my Japanese is not so good. If possible, can a person who can speak English (just a little bit is fine) contact me to talk about a possible collaboration?  \n    Warm Regards Rob Oudendijk\n    \n\n**2025-10-06** made phone call after no replies. Not so good communications.
2	3	13	Bioamass power	<br>\n\n**Aridagawa, Wakayama Prefecture** [https://www.chuden.co.jp/english/corporate/releases/pressreleases/1207477\\_5163.html](https://www.chuden.co.jp/english/corporate/releases/pressreleases/1207477_5163.html)\n\n**Aridagawa Biomass K.K.:** A wood gasification power plant in Aridagawa designed for local resource efficiency, which began operations in August 2022, supplying power and heat for local needs. [https://maps.app.goo.gl/YwBM5NJwpzxLyCLr6](https://maps.app.goo.gl/YwBM5NJwpzxLyCLr6)\n\n**Distributed AI Trend:** Government initiatives are currently pushing for [smaller, urban-scale AI facilities](https://www.intralinkgroup.com/latest/intralink-insights/thinking-small-the-international-tech-making-japans-urban-data-center-strategy-possible) that can move workloads to where power—including biomass—is most available [https://www.intralinkgroup.com/latest/intralink-insights/thinking-small-the-international-tech-making-japans-urban-data-center-strategy-possible](https://www.intralinkgroup.com/latest/intralink-insights/thinking-small-the-international-tech-making-japans-urban-data-center-strategy-possible)\n\n<br>
3	3	13	Ryokichi Hirono	### **Notes to be done:**\n\nDirect contact information such as a personal email address or phone number for Dr. Ryokichi Hirono is not publicly available in the provided sources\n\nHowever, you can try to reach him through the organizations he is affiliated with:\n\n*   **The Japan Forum on International Relations (JFIR):** Dr. Hirono is listed as a researcher here. You may be able to send an inquiry through their general contact details.\n    \n    *   **Address:** 2-17-12-1301, Akasaka, Minato-ku, Tokyo, 107-0052\n        \n    *   **Phone:** +813-3584-2190\n        \n    *   **Fax:** +813-3589-5120\n        \n    *   [JFIR Website](https://www.jfir.or.jp/en/researcher/2610/)\n        \n*   **Association for Promotion of International Cooperation (APIC):** He serves as a Trustee for this organization.\n    \n    *   APIC Website (General contact details may be available elsewhere on their site).\n        \n*   **East Asia Forum:** He is an author for this publication. You might be able to contact them regarding author inquiries.\n    \n    *   [East Asia Forum Website](https://eastasiaforum.org/author/ryokichihirono/)\n        \n*   **SAGE Publications:** He is an author with this publisher.&nbsp;\n    \n\nTo contact Dr. Ryokichi Hirono, you may be able to reach him through the professional organizations with which he is associated, or possibly use a personal email address that has been publicly linked to him in older documents\n\nContact Options\n\n*   **Email:** A publicly available email address found in a 2010 UNESCAP document is ryokichi\\_hirono@yahoo.co.jp. This email may no longer be active, so use at your discretion.\n    \n*   **Seikei University:** As he is a Professor Emeritus, the university may not provide direct contact information. However, you could try contacting the Economics department or the general university contact information and ask if they can forward a professional inquiry. You can find general contact information on the university&#39;s official website.\n    \n*   **Associated Organizations:** Dr. Hirono has been actively involved with several international cooperation and evaluation organizations. Reaching out to these organizations for professional inquiries may be a viable option:
